Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{1%tbsp}, season with @salt and @pepper then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1}. Reserve 1 leaf per person, halve the remaining lettuce lengthways, then thinly slice widthways. Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the onion to the pan and cook until softened, ~{6-8%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

Meanwhile, halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125} and finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(finely chopped, stalks and all). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}. Remove the stalk from the @portobello mushrooms{2} (but leave the mushroom whole).

Once the onion has cooked, transfer to a #bowl{}. Return the frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Add the mushrooms to the pan and season with salt and pepper. Fry until golden brown, ~{3-4%minutes}, then turn over and cook for a further ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once the potatoes have about 10 mins left, move them to the middle of the oven. Transfer the mushrooms (stalk side up) onto a baking tray. Divide the cheddar between the mushrooms then bake on the top shelf of your oven until the cheese has melted, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the tomatoes, parsley, sliced baby gem, @olive oil{1%tbsp} and @red wine vinegar{12%ml} into a bowl. Season with salt, pepper and a pinch of @?sugar{pinch}. Mix together and set aside.

Halve the @glazed burger buns{2}. Add the @BBQ sauce{64%ml} to the onions and stir together.

Pop your burger buns into your oven to warm through for the last ~{1-2%minutes} of mushroom cooking time. Divide the buns between your plates and top the bottom half with a whole baby gem leaf and the cheesy mushroom. Spoon over the BBQ onions and top with the bun lid. Serve with the wedges and salad alongside. Enjoy!